<TITLE> Brazil pair out, Mexico debut for Dos Santos </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 RIO DE JANEIRO, Sept 7 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Soccer news in brief from around the world. Chelsea centre half Alex and Sao Paulo defender Alex Silva are out of Brazil's friendlies against United States and Mexico because of injury, the Brazilian Football Confederation (CBF) said. The pair have been replaced by Edu Dracena of Fenerbahce and Gladstone of Sporting Lisbon. Brazil face the U.S. in Chicago on Sunday and Mexico in Boston three days later. Giovani dos Santos, 18, will make his Mexico debut in Sunday's home friendly against Panama in Puebla. "I don't usually give the line-up in advance but I can tell you Giovani will make his debut," coach Hugo Sanchez told reporters. Dos Santos, who joined Barcelona as a 13-year-old, is seen as one of Mexico's great hopes for the future
